1. PURPOSE
================================================================================
This Incident Response Plan provides a structured approach for detecting,
containing, eradicating, and recovering from cybersecurity incidents.

2. INCIDENT RESPONSE TEAM
================================================================================
| Role | Responsibility | Contact |
|------|----------------|---------|
| Incident Commander | Overall coordination | [Name/Title] |
| Security Lead | Technical analysis | [Name/Title] |
| IT Lead | System restoration | [Name/Title] |
| Communications Lead | Internal/External comms | [Name/Title] |
| Legal Lead | Compliance/Legal review | [Name/Title] |
| HR Lead | Employee matters | [Name/Title] |

3. INCIDENT CLASSIFICATION
================================================================================
| Severity | Description | Examples |
|----------|-------------|----------|
| P1 - Critical | Severe business impact | Data breach, ransomware, major outage |
| P2 - High | Significant impact | Phishing success, system compromise |
| P3 - Medium | Limited impact | Malware on single system, unauthorized access |
| P4 - Low | Minimal impact | Suspicious activity, policy violation |

4. RESPONSE PHASES
================================================================================
PHASE 1: DETECTION (P1/P2 Incidents)
- Identify potential incident
- Verify through log analysis
- Document initial findings
- Assign classification
- Activate response team

PHASE 2: CONTAINMENT
- Isolate affected systems
- Block malicious traffic
- Change passwords/access
- Preserve evidence
- Document all actions

PHASE 3: ERADICATION
- Remove malware/backdoors
- Apply security patches
- Rebuild affected systems
- Verify system integrity
- Update security controls

PHASE 4: RECOVERY
- Restore from backups
- Test system functionality
- Monitor for recurrence
- Return to normal operations
- Update incident status

PHASE 5: POST-INCIDENT
- Conduct lessons learned
- Update response plan
- Implement improvements
- Document final report
- Notify stakeholders

5. COMMUNICATION PLAN
================================================================================
| Stakeholder | Communication Channel | Timing |
|-------------|----------------------|--------|
| Internal Team | Microsoft Teams | Immediate |
| Management | Phone/Email | Within 1 hour |
| Legal Counsel | Phone/Email | Within 2 hours |
| Insurance Provider | Phone | Within 4 hours |
| NITDA (Regulator) | Formal Letter | Within 72 hours |
| Clients (if affected) | Formal Letter | Within 48 hours |

6. TECHNICAL RESPONSE PROCEDURES
================================================================================
RANSOMWARE RESPONSE:
1. Isolate infected systems (disconnect network)
2. Contain spread (block network traffic)
3. Assess encryption (identify impact)
4. Contact IR team immediately
5. Do NOT pay ransom
6. Restore from clean backups

PHISHING RESPONSE:
1. Block sender/domain
2. Reset affected user passwords
3. Remove malicious emails
4. Analyze for compromise
5. Conduct user training

DATA BREACH RESPONSE:
1. Contain access (revoke credentials)
2. Preserve evidence (logs, backups)
3. Determine scope and impact
4. Notify affected parties
5. Engage legal counsel
6. Report to NITDA

7. TESTING AND EXERCISES
================================================================================
| Frequency | Exercise Type | Participants |
|-----------|---------------|--------------|
| Quarterly | Tabletop Exercise | All team members |
| Annually | Full Simulation | All team members |
| Biannual | Phishing Simulation | All employees |

8. PLAN MAINTENANCE
================================================================================
- Review plan annually
- Update contact information
- Update based on lessons learned
- Maintain incident documentation

